- Nitrile group (C#N): The nitrile functional group also tends to raise the melting point by increasing polarity and promoting dipolar interactions. An adjustment increase of about +40°C might be appropriate.

Adding these adjustments to the basic thiophene unit estimate should give a rough approximation of the actual melting point for 2-nitrothiophene-4-carbonitrile.
